cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SI 

This paper discusses the evaluation of Android malware detection methods, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of different labeling schemes and the impact of time on the performance of the detection methods, which could be relevant to software engineering (cs.SE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of an ensemble of detection methods could also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and the evaluation of detection methods could be relevant to systems and information theory (cs.SI).
